sys_hub_action_type_definition.description:
Gets the access control policy for a resource.

Inputs:

  • Project ID - Unique ID of the project.
  • Zone - Name of the zone.
  • Instance - Name of the instance.

Outputs:

  • IAM Policy - IObject containing Bindings, Role, Members, Condition, Etag, and Version.
  • Status - If the request is executed successfully, Status is set to “Success”. If there is a failure in Google Compute Engine, Status is set to “Error".
  • Error Message - Reason for error. Populated only when an error occurs.

Error Messages:

  • Invalid instance.
  • Invalid Project ID.
  • Invalid authorization header. The access token you're using is either expired or invalid.

To use this action, a corresponding Google Compute Engine connection and credential must be created and associated with the Google Compute Engine Connection & Credential alias. Learn More

Note: Requires a subscription for production use. Read More.
